# env-and-secrets.mdc

- Access secrets only in server contexts (Route Handlers, Server Actions, server components, and other server-only modules).
- Never pass secret values to Client Components or prefix secret names with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` only for values that are safe to expose to browsers.
- Document required environment variables in `.env.example` (or the project’s documented location) without committing real secrets.
